02/07/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Police arrested 32 people on Thursday (July 1st) for suspected drug dealing and weapons smuggling, during a series of early morning raids, mainly in Republika Srpska. 
In all, about 400 police officers participated in the arrests, raiding about 40 homes. 
(RTS, RTRS, SRNA - 01/07/10)
